Introduction:

This website was developed as a course project for EG6328 - Software Engineering - at St. Mary's University. The inspiritaion behind this idea is that we wanted to create a centralized point of contact for students, tutors, and professors. This site offers a convenient all-in-one-place for students to contact each in a private and secure manner regarding course material such as lecture notes and recordings, questions, and/or quiz/exam reviews.





Implementation:

To build this website we used the 'big three' in front-end web development - JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS. To develop the user interface we took advantage of the open-source JS library known as React; this allowed us to create an elegant interface as well as various UI components that we integrated into this website. Regarding backend we decided to use MySQL to store and transfer user data such as id #'s, names, emails for weekly subscribers, and passwords.
